      "stem_html": "<p>One of the steps in fatty-acid biosynthesis is the dehydration of (<i>R</i>)-3-hydroxybutyryl ACP to give <i>trans</i>-crotonyl ACP. Does the reaction remove the pro-<i>R</i> or the pro-<i>S</i> hydrogen from C2?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdWtZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--6bc528e3640839b1d36ace83e0b8556f2b0901ba/OChem_05_EC_025.jpg\" alt=\"The dehydration of (R)-3-hydroxybutyryl A C P to form trans-crotonyl A C P.\">",
